<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="915" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d915">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hardy</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-28"><hi rend="italic">May 28,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hardy reports that the Swiss Government has granted permission for
                            United States consular officers within its jurisdiction to exercise good
                            offices in behalf of Cuban interests, and that notification of this
                            permission has been transmitted to consuls.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>